The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             The City Diary
                Consumers can avail themselves of another direct-to-home (DTH) service with the launch of Reliance Communicationss Big TV on Thursday. Big TV will be the fourth player along with Doordarshan Direct, Tata Sky and Dish TV. Our MPEG 4-enabled technology platform will allow us to beam 202 channels to begin with, said Sanjay Behl, the group head (brands and marketing), Reliance Communications.     The decomposing body of a 55-year-old man, Bahadur, was discovered in his house in Sonarpur by police on Thursday morning. Local residents called the cops after a foul smell started emanating from his house. The body has been sent for post-mortem.    An unidentified man in his early 40s was killed on Thursday morning when a lorry hit him on CGR Road, near Satya Doctor Road crossing. Police said the lorry dashed the man while he was crossing the road. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he succumbed to his injuries.    Members of Posta Goods Transport Operators Association put up a roadblock at the crossing of Kali Krishna Tagore Street and Strand Road on Thursday afternoon protesting the atrocities of Wednesdays bandh supporters. Transport operator Krishna Pratap Singh alleged that he was manhandled and his goods were damaged when he refused to close his office during the bandh. The roadblock was withdrawn after 30 minutes when officers from Posta police station intervened.    An unattended bag lying near the domestic terminal building of Calcutta airport caused a bomb scare on Thursday. The black bag was spotted by CISF personnel around 9.20am. An announcement was made over the public address system, but when no one claimed the bag, the area was cordoned off and the bomb disposal squad was called in. A search revealed that the bag contained clothes.     An Air India flight to Silchar was delayed by nearly three hours on Thursday morning because of a snag. It was scheduled to take off around 6.55am but left around 9.50am.                                                                                                                                                              
